query: Research quantum computing breakthroughs announced August 2024 to November 2024. Context: Finding major technical and commercial developments in quantum computing over the last 3 months. Goal: Identify top breakthroughs with exact announcement dates and technical details. Focus areas: 1) Error correction and fidelity improvements, 2) Hardware scaling (qubit counts, new architectures), 3) Commercial applications and product releases, 4) Academic research from major institutions. Success criteria: Each breakthrough must have exact date, source attribution, and specific technical metrics. Constraints: Only August 2024 or later, prioritize official announcements from IBM/Google/IonQ/academic journals.
